items.name: FeiWu废物
items.description:
声明：模型禁止任何形式的转载和二次发布，供学习参考经验交流，可自由融模，谨遵当地法律法规，不得用于商用或其他非法用途。

The model prohibits any form of reproduction and secondary publication. It is for learning, reference and experience exchange. Please abide by local laws and regulations and do not use it for commercial or other illegal purposes.

v0：动漫类型的融模，效果为强调线条感，但由于过分强调也导致直出图片会糊图，结合高清修复使用效果良好，属于是其他子版本的基础模型。

v1-Dline：（旧命名为2.5D）基于v0进行融合调整，一定程度上修复了v0直出糊图的问题，效果上强调线条感（detailed line），特色挺强，检验过读tag能力和图片质量可适用于各种用法。此模型可以文生图直出不会糊图，兼容各种采样器，无需捆绑采样器和高修算法使用。此模型内置anime的vae。注意，不适合使用840000的vae，会导致糊图以及轮廓破坏的问题，如选择外挂clip建议使用anime或者是clear的vae。

v1-SlightFlat：这个版本的效果有些许偏向平涂风，并且兼容了少女幼态（没有做过关于男性的测试），能出可爱类型的人物。

v1-FlatCoating：基于SlightFlat进一步调整，相比于SlightFlat进一步强化了平涂风格，是纯纯的平涂风格动画类模型，同样兼容可爱类型的人物出图。

（目前就更这么多，不同效果的v1子分支在测试中，后续更新会放出来）

The Dline fusion model emphasizes the sense of line in effect, has a similar sharpening feeling, has strong characteristics, and can be applied to various uses after testing the ability to read tags and picture quality. This model can be straight out of the text without paste, compatible with various samplers, without the need to bundle samplers and advanced repair algorithms. This model has a built-in VAE for anime, note that the VAE of the 840000 is not suitable.

（PS: v0 Need to use Hires. fix）

items.name: Easy sticker
items.description:
Подписывайтесь на канал, я там рассказываю как работать со stable diffusion

Info

This LoRa was created to reproduce cartoonish style and plain background. Works well with range of models and other LoRA's.
Trained on v1-5-pruned with vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned using 110 default telegram stickers (both colorful and monochrome versions)

Colorful: https://chpic.su/en/stickers/GreatMindsColor/ (add stickers link https://t.me/addstickers/GreatMindsColor)
Monochrome: https://chpic.su/en/stickers/AntiqueGreatMinds/ (add stickers link https://t.me/addstickers/AntiqueGreatMinds)
You can check out example sticker pack, created with this LoRA https://t.me/addstickers/sd_easy_sticker

Trigger words

sticker, monochrome, color
Also both color styles can be added to negative prompt, for example if images look's kinda unsaturated, add monochrome to negative and vice versa.

I highly recommend to add die-cut sticker, {main object} sticker, sample background and if it is needed cartoon, minimalism, solid outline.

Settings

Sampler: Euler a
Steps: 20-40 (depends on model and other LoRa's your use)
CFG: 5-7 (again, depends on model and other LoRa's your use)
LoRA weight: 0.8-1.3 (you can start with 1.0 and adjust for your case)

All examples were generated with Dreamshaper and AnythingV3

Workflow example

  1. Generate sticker you like

  2. (this step may be skipped) Upscale, I used R-ESRGAN AnimeVideo

  3. Remove background with your favourite image editing software (I used Photoshop) or rembg, for example

  4. Fix outline or minor defects

Sketch mode also gives us decent results in one step (from sketch to final image) as well as iterative (when you pass your initial sketch with low denoising and use it as your new sketch)

Общее

Сделал лору, чтобы было проще делать стикеры. Она добавляет мультяшного вида и однотонный фон. Хорошо работает с большинством моделей и другими лорами.

Тренировал на v1-5-pruned с vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned используя 110 дефолтных телеграмовских стикера (включая цветные и монохромные версии)

Цветные: https://chpic.su/en/stickers/GreatMindsColor/ (ссылка чтобы добавить стикеры https://t.me/addstickers/GreatMindsColor)
Монохромные: https://chpic.su/en/stickers/AntiqueGreatMinds/ (ссылка чтобы добавить стикеры https://t.me/addstickers/AntiqueGreatMinds)
Тестовый стикерпак, который сделал с этой лорой https://t.me/addstickers/sd_easy_sticker

Ключевые слова

sticker, monochrome, color
Обе расцветки можно добавить в негатив, например, если картинка выглядит ненасыщенной, то можно добавить monochrome в негатив и наоборот.

Рекомендую добавить в промпт die-cut sticker, {основной объект/субъект} sticker, sample background и если нужно, то можно добавить cartoon, minimalism, solid outline.

Настройки

Jennifer Love Hewitt (born February 21, 1979[2]) is an American actress and singer. Hewitt began her career as a child actress and singer, appearing in national television commercials before joining the cast of the Disney Channel series Kids Incorporated (1989–1991). She had her breakthrough as Sarah Reeves Merrin on the Fox teen drama Party of Five (1995–1999) and rose to fame as a teen star for her role as Julie James in the horror films I Know What You Did Last Summer (1997) and its 1998 sequel, as well as her role as Amanda Beckett in the teen comedy film Can't Hardly Wait (1998).

Hewitt's other notable films include Heartbreakers (2001), The Tuxedo (2002) and the two Garfield live-action films (2004–2006). She has starred as Melinda Gordon on the CBS supernatural drama Ghost Whisperer (2005–2010), Riley Parks on the Lifetime drama series The Client List (2012–2013), Special Agent Kate Callahan on the CBS crime drama Criminal Minds (2014–2015), and since 2018, Maddie Buckley on the Fox first-responder procedural 9-1-1. She was nominated for the Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Miniseries or Television Film for The Client List pilot film (2010).

In music, Hewitt has released four studio albums to date. After her debut album, Love Songs (1992), was released at age 12 exclusively in Japan, she went on to record Let's Go Bang (1995), Jennifer Love Hewitt (1996) and BareNaked (2002), the latter of which became her first album to chart in the United States, peaking at number 37 on the Billboard 200 chart. Her most successful single on the Billboard Hot 100 chart was the 1999 release "How Do I Deal", which peaked at number 59.[3] In addition to music and acting, Hewitt has served as a producer on some of her film and television projects. She has appeared in several magazines' lists of the world's most beautiful women.

items.name: Ralph Steadman Style
items.description:
Ralph Steadman is a British artist and illustrator known for his distinctive and often highly satirical artwork.

His style can be described as bold, frenetic, and characterized by exaggerated lines, splatters, and expressive brushwork. Steadman's artwork often features grotesque and distorted figures, emphasizing the darker and absurd aspects of human nature.

He gained significant recognition for his collaborations with the American journalist and author Hunter S. Thompson, most notably illustrating Thompson's book "Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas." Steadman's illustrations for the book became iconic, capturing the chaotic and hallucinatory nature of Thompson's writing.

Steadman's art often incorporates elements of social and political commentary. He uses his unique visual language to critique authority, corruption, and hypocrisy in society, often employing dark humor and satire to convey his messages.

His illustrations have appeared in books, magazines, newspapers, and advertisements, and his work has been exhibited internationally. Steadman's artwork extends beyond traditional illustrations, including paintings, sculptures, and prints.

Ralph Steadman's distinctive and unapologetic style has made him a highly influential figure in the world of illustration and political art. His ability to capture the essence of the human condition through his raw and unfiltered visuals continues to resonate with audiences, challenging societal norms and provoking thought.

items.name: Emmanuelle Béart (80s)
items.description:
Emmanuelle Béart (born 14 August 1963) is a French actress, who has appeared in over 60 film and television productions since 1972. An eight-time César Award nominee, she won the César Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1986 film Manon des Sources. Her other film roles include La Belle Noiseuse (1991), A Heart in Winter (1992), Nelly and Mr. Arnaud (1995), Mission: Impossible (1996) and 8 Women (2002).

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, well, it's on you.

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : EB, a woman, photography, trending on artstation, sharp focus, studio photo, intricate details, highly detailed, by greg rutkowski <lora:EBeart:0.9>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use EB as trigger.

items.name: Poses Packs Collection
items.description:
Patreon

Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

IMPORTANT: Remember to check image sizes and use these proportions or you might not get what you want.

Install Instructions:

open stable diffusion -> extensions -> install from URL -> https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet.git

click Apply and restart UI

Then download from https://huggingface.co/webui/ControlNet-modules-safetensors/tree/main the file control_depth-fp16.safetensor, control_openpose-fp16.safetensor control_canny-fp16.safetensor

place it inside extensions/sd-webui-controlnet/models

After all of this, you will have a ControlNet v1.1.112 just above Script in txt2image tab

Open it, place the pose (black and white image with depths is depth, black images with colored sticks is openpose, black and white images like drawing is canny, not the example one) you want to replicate by selecting it from your computer and place it in the image selection square box. You can also drag and drop.

Select preprocessor NONE, check Enable Checkbox, select control_depth-fp16 or openpose or canny (it depends on wich poses you downloaded, look at version to see wich kind of pose is it if you don't recognize it in Model list) check Controlnet is more important in Control Mode (or leave balanced).

Then generate your image, don't forget to write a proper prompt for the image and to preserve the proportions of the controlnet image (you can just check proportions in the example images for example).

I uploaded the pose images and 1 example generated image with that pose using the same prompt for all of them. But you can modify the prompt to fit what you want.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: Uesugi Kenshin (Rance series)
items.description:
For my second LoRA, another fan (and personal) favorite from the Rance games.
I'm pretty happy with how it turned out, my training data was heavily skewed towards her armored appearance, so those look pretty good as expected, but her clothing is more flexible than I anticipated, so that was a pleasant surprise. The only weaker point I saw is with explicit NSFW, I found that the nsfw tag messes with the quality a bit, so try to omit it if possible, otherwise it works fine, but it's not the main focus of this Lora (maybe in a future version).

Weight around 0.75 worked best for me.

The activation tag is uesugi kenshin (rance), which should cover her general appearance.
For her armored look these are useful: armor, helmet, hair ribbon.

modelVersions.name: Long Hime Cut
modelVersions.description:
As you can see many of my images have a perfect hime cut hairstyle not showing the fronthead, in those images i used my model in inpaint, first i generated the images as i wanted, then i sent to inpaint, masked the fronthead, checked fill checkbox and wrote in the prompt only this: "(long_hime_cut_hairstyle:1.3),<lora:long_hime_cut_hairstyle:0.5>" and then generated to have a perfect hime cut hairstyle.

I didn't do that for all the images, some of them are just generated, but they are not perfect hime cuts. So, remeber to inpaint if the generations is not how you want it.

Remember if you are inpainting an image after the other that before sending to inpaint your image you have to close the last image from img2img or in the new generation it will remember the old masked part other then the masked part of your new image, doing a mess.

Also many of the images are generated using controlnet poses packs that you can find in my page.

Works also with anime.

items.name: [GUIDE] How to Use AingDiffusion Models
items.description:
YOU DON'T NEED TO DOWNLOAD ANYTHING. THE GUIDE IS BELOW

AingDiffusion-Guide

This is a readme file designed to provide a simple guide on how to use AingDiffusion models effectively.

Introduction

AingDiffusion (pronounced as "Ah-eeng Diffusion") is a combination of various anime models. It is a powerful model that can generate high-quality anime images. The term "aing" is derived from the informal Sundanese language spoken in West Java, Indonesia. It translates to "I" or "my." The name signifies that this model produces images that align with my personal taste.

How to Use the Model

This tutorial can be applied to other models as well and is not specific to AingDiffusion. Before proceeding, please ensure that you have the latest version of AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion WebUI installed. To begin, follow these steps:

  1. Save the desired model to the models directory, located at [YOUR_SDWEBUI_DIR]\models\Stable-diffusion. For example, if you are using the Stable Diffusion model, save it to [YOUR_SDWEBUI_DIR]\models\Stable-diffusion.

  1. Save the VAE (Variational Autoencoder) in the [YOUR_SDWEBUI_DIR]\models\VAE directory.

Adjust the Clip Skip to 2

After launching the WebUI, navigate to the Settings tab.

Once in the settings tab, click on Stable Diffusion on the left side of the page. This will take you to the Stable Diffusion settings. Scroll down and locate the setting labeled "Clip Skip." Set its value to 2.

Specify the VAE

On the same page, you will find a setting called SD VAE. Select the VAE you downloaded from AingDiffusion. If the VAE does not appear in the list, click the Refresh button next to the list box to update the VAE list.

Set ENSD (Eta Noise Seed Delta) to 31337

Switch to the "Sampler Parameters" tab. On the left side of the page, click on Sampler Parameters. Scroll down until you find the setting labeled "Eta noise seed delta." Set its value to 31337. This number originated from the leaked NovelAI model and is still commonly used.

Adjust Eta (Noise Multiplier) for Ancestral Samplers to 0.667

On the same page, locate the setting labeled "Eta (noise multiplier) for ancestral samplers." Change its value to 0.667.

This setting will improve the performance of ancestral samplers such as Euler a.

Prompting

AingDiffusion new merges (v2.0 and up) has Counterfeit v3.0 integrated in it. This make the model sometimes have better performance using natural language prompts.

masterpiece, best quality, a girl sitting at a pool side, short hair, silver hair, blue eyes, swimsuit, smile, large breasts, from side,

masterpiece, best quality, 1girl, poolside, sitting, short hair, silver hair, blue eyes, swimsuit, smile, large breasts, from side,

As you can see from the 2 images above, the hands with natural language prompting is better than the full booru-tags one. Let me give another example.

masterpiece, best quality, a girl with long blonde hair and blue eyes looking up, forest, from above,
masterpiece, best quality, 1girl, long hair, blonde hair, blue eyes, looking up, forest, from above,

The left hand is as worst. But look at the right hand. It's way better on the first image with natural language prompts.

Disclaimer

Please note that this guide does not provide an exhaustive list of settings for optimizing SD-WebUI for image generation. There are many other potential improvements that can be made by adjusting the settings. Please feel free to explore and experiment with different configurations to achieve the desired results.

items.name: 2009 Touhou Fanart
items.description:
The dataset for this one is 20 images from pixiv.net.

All of them are fanart of Remilia Scarlet from the Touhou Project game series.

Come to think of it, I should have thrown in her official art as well.

Well, anyway, all the dataset images are of Remilia, but since it's a LoCon, it can actually be pretty flexible and make any character look like they're from a 2009 fanart image.

It can work well combined with my HL2 Concept Art LoRA.

This model can be a bit picky; when I tested it on profantasy_v2, it would only work with a unet weight of 0.5 or lower, but on dreamshaper_4BakedVae, it would work at any weight.

It seems to work best on models that have at least a basic amount of training on Touhou-related images.

I created this model - and the HL2 concept art one! - because I love the various art styles of the 2000s, and even before the advent of NovelAI I was lamenting at how art had become so homogenous in style and flatly lit.

You even see it in video games these days. A wall texture is no longer a detailed surface, it's just a solid colour with some faint brush strokes. It may be easier to pick out players this way, but it's also stylistically bankrupt while claiming to be the opposite. Just criminal.

items.name: Kira Thorn MoC+
items.description:
‼ IMPORTANT ‼

  • Your voice matters! Show your support and leave a post, comment and most importantly a review! ⭐

  • Custom LORAs available upon request. Just buymeacoffee.☕

  • This is a + LORA! (details in workflow advice below)

  • 👇(workflow advice below) 👇

📝Biography📝

🌟Kira Thorn🌟

is a Russian film actress and model, born on June 9th, 1995 in Russia. She began her career in the entertainment industry in 2016 at the age of 21. Kira is mainly known for her acting in videos and web scenes.

Kira has also performed in videos with various famous actresses such as Cathy Heaven, Isabella Clark, and Emily Ross. She has gained popularity for her attractive figure and confidence. Kira's measurements are 34A-23-34, and she stands at 5'3" (160 cm) and weighs 105lbs (48 kg). Her body has a slim figure with natural and perfect 34A breasts. She has captivating brown eyes and thick blonde/auburn hair.

Kira Thorn is a travel and shopping enthusiast who loves taking selfies and surfing the internet. She is also a dog lover. Kira's favorite clothing brands include Calvin Klein, LOUIS VUITTON, Tommy Hilfiger, and Levi Strauss & Co.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .9 - 1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • This + series is something new, let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

  • Help me help you: Leave a review if you've used this LORA.

  • Most of my gens are not voodoo or outside of workflows I've indicated here or in my other posts.

    • In other words: Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond with suggestions.
